{
  "uuid": "a1822b583dc7171e083407b7ddf0b583",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Safety/WSH Coordinator",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Good knowledge on WSH Act and Other regulatory requirements</li><li>Daily Safety toolbox meeting, prepare & maintain equipment, safety records etc.</li><li>Conduct regular site inspections and rectify any unsafe practices and conditions at the worksite</li><li>Conduct and organize regular in–house Safety training</li><li>Ensure all site activities adhere to legal regulations and including WSH regulations</li><li>Work with SIC manager to monitor compliance & Identify Safety issues</li><li>Carry out effective Safety supervision to prevent re-work</li><li>Able to carry out investigate incident, accident, dangerous occurrence or non-compliance that occurred at the worksite</li><li>Identify, conduct & prepare risk assessment, method statement, JHA etc. in accordance worksite activities requirement</li><li>Able to develop and implement Safety Action Plan/Program in line with Company/Client WSH/HSE manual/program</li><li>Establish good working relation with Client/Owner Safety personnel of their concerns and programs to be implemented</li><li>Identify, Intervene in unsafe activities or operations</li><li>Able to exercise reasonably, practicable analytical judgement and work independently</li><li>Able to carry other tasks or ad-hoc assignment as where required or assigned</li><li>Proficient to work with computer using MS office suite competently</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum Higher Secondary Level with a Pass in English, Math and Science or Qualification</li><li>Minimum 2-3 years’ experience in Oil & Gas, Petrochemical and or related industries work as Safety</li><li>WSQ - Advanced Certificate in WSH (Level B) or Equivalent (Safety Coordinator Training Course)</li><li>WSQ - Supervise Workplace Safety and Health in Process Plant or Equivalent (OPSIC)</li><li>WSQ - Manage Work at Height (Supervisor)</li><li>WSQ - Supervise Work in Confined Space (Supervisor)</li><li>BizSafe Level 2: Risk Management</li><li>Good Oral & written communication skills</li><li>Good initiative & analytical skills</li><li>Proactive and highly motivated individual</li><li>Possess a Class 2 (Motorbike) or 3 License (If have)</li><li>Willing to work in Jurong Area</li></ul><p><em><strong>Remuneration will subject to qualifications, certificates and work experiences (Relevant)</strong></em></p>",
